 Palmietfontein - Police in Palmietfontein have appealed to the public for assistance with information that can help them find a missing 17-year-old girl, Motshehetsi Lebesa. "She was reported missing on the 24 September 2019 after she went to visit her grandmother on the 20 September 2019 at Hohobeng a/a," police said. "Lebesa left her grandmother's home after the holiday as the school was about to re-open, but she never reached Musing a/a. She was wearing a white t-shirt, blue jeans and a red bandana on her head by the time she left her grandmother's home." Police said that if any person can assist with information on her disappearance they must please contact D/W/O Languza Palmietfontein Detectives at 051-6111 909 or 082 44 22 276. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 